This is a help-file which contains miscellaneous information about
role-playing. Some things to avoid, some terms etc. Please read on.

Terms used in Role-Playing

RP- Short for "role-playing"

RoLL-Playing - Term for those who are obsessed with Stats, eq, killing etc.
A bad RoLE-player. Someone who does not role-play. Synonym for "Power-Muder"

OOC - Stands for "Out of Character", a statement or action which is NOT
Role-playing. The opposite of role-playing.

Things to avoid when role-playing

-Mentioning and obsessing about things which are not really part of the
game, such as "stats", "eq", "levels" and "xp", is bad practice. If someone
mentions these to you, either kindly inform them it's horrid role-playing,
or mess with their minds and reply "Pardon me good sir? Xp? I know not of
what thou are speaking? Is it some horrid beast that has appeared out of
town?! My Word! Run! Run for your lives! Xp is coming!" etc.

-Blatantly telling other people who your other characters are. This is of
course sometimes necessary, when dealing with family lines and children, but
this is the only exception. NEVER tell someone you're X char in hopes of
getting a break, NEVER tell someone you're X character in OOC chatter, if
they ask, tell them it's not really good role-playing to ask. NEVER tell
other people you know that X person also plays character Y and Z. Why is
this a taboo? Think on it, letting everyone know you play this, that and
them, it will affect how they react to you in a way which has no basis in
role-playing.

-Letting your own personality dominate your character. Try to forget you're
you when playing, pretend you ARE your character. That's the core of good
role-playing.

-Leave the real world out of it. Don't mention things like Computers, lag,
internet, world-wide-web etc. While playing the game.

